ch an organism initiates, promotes, or enhances vasodilation via the action of a venom that prevents angiotensin maturation, concomittantly reducing blood pressure in the bitten/stung organism.\" [PMID:31370142]\nsynonym: \"venom-mediated vasodilation mediated by inhibition of angiotensin-converting enzyme\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"venom-mediated vasodilation through perturbation of angiotensin maturation\" EXACT []\nis_a: GO:0044509 ! venom-mediated perturbation of signal transduction\nis_a: GO:0044551 ! venom-mediated vasodilation\nrelationship: negatively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0002003 ! angiotensin maturation\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30014\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2025-04-01T09:46:06Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0140183\nname: venom-mediated vasoconstriction via activation of endothelin receptor signaling pathway\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which an organism promotes the narrowing (constriction) of blood vessels, by inhibiting the widening (dilation) of blood vessels in another organism via the action of a venom that activates endothelin receptor signaling pathway, concomittantly increasing blood pressure in the bitten/stung organism.\" [PMID:16277978]\nsynonym: \"venom-mediated vasoconstriction via activation of endothelin signaling pathway\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"venom-mediated vasoconstriction via activation of endothelin-dependent signaling\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"venom-mediated vasoconstriction via endothelin receptor agonism\" EXACT []\nintersection_of: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biological process\nintersection_of: positively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0086100 ! endothelin receptor signaling pathway\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30211\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2025-06-26T08:05:09Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0140184\nname: venom-mediated suppression of blood coagulation, intrinsic pathway\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which an organism inhibits or disrupts blood coagulation in another organism by suppression of the intrinsic pathway via the action of a venom. A common mechanism is the blocking the activity of host coagulation Factor XIIa (F12).\" [PMID:25724270]\nsynonym: \"venom-mediated suppression of blood coagulation cascade, contact activation system\" EXACT []\nintersection_of: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biological process\nintersection_of: negatively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0007597 ! blood coagulation, intrinsic pathway\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30519\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2025-06-27T13:34:32Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0140342\nname: venom-mediated perturbation of heart contraction\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which an organism alters or subverts the heart contractility in another organism via the action of a venom.\" [PMID:38167790]\nintersection_of: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biological process\nintersection_of: regulates_in_another_organism GO:0060047 ! heart contraction\nrelationship: regulates_in_another_organism GO:0008015 ! blood circulation\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31096\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2025-11-20T10:56:34Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0140548\nname: obsolete venom-mediated platelet agglutination\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"OBSOLETE. A process in which an organism initiates, promotes, or enhances platelet agglutination in another organism via the action of a venom. This may takes place is via specific proteins binding to cell-surface carbohydrates on the platelet's cell membrane, resulting in calcium-dependent agglutination.\" [PMID:10484740, PMID:28435120]\ncomment: This term was obsoleted because it represents the same process as venom-mediated platelet aggregation ; GO:0044478.\nsynonym: \"envenomation resulting in blood agglutination in another organism\" BROAD []\nsynonym: \"envenomation resulting in blood agglutination in other organism\" BROAD []\nsynonym: \"venom-mediated blood agglutination\" BROAD []\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/18979\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\nreplaced_by: GO:0044478\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2020-11-11T21:42:31Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0141123\nname: venom-mediated dermonecrosis in another organism\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"The disruption of the skin of another organism, leading to damage or temporary subversion of the skin.\" [PMID:28194160]\nis_a: GO:0140138 ! venom-mediated disruption of anatomical structure in another organism\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26513\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2023-12-01T15:13:15Z\n\n","metadata":{"output":"...\n\nm-mediated perturbation of biological process\nintersection_of: positively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0007186 ! G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29564\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29851\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: jl\ncreation_date: 2012-02-26T11:06:15Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0044521\nname: venom-mediated muscle damage in another organism\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process that begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, and ends with resultant muscle damage in the bitten organism.\" [GOC:fj, GOC:jl, PMID:10620318, PMID:21150580]\nsynonym: \"envenomation resulting in muscle damage in another organism\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"envenomation resulting in muscle damage in other organism\" EXACT []\nis_a: GO:0140138 ! venom-mediated disruption of anatomical structure in another organism\ncreated_by: jl\ncreation_date: 2012-02-27T12:31:08Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0044522\nname: venom-mediated myocyte killing in another organism\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process that begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, killing heart myocytes and ultimately resulting in muscle damage in the bitten organism.\" [GOC:fj, GOC:jl, PMID:10620318, PMID:21150580]\nsynonym: \"envenomation resulting in myocyte killing causing muscle damage in other organism\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"envenomation resulting in myocyte killing in another organism\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"envenomation resulting in myocyte killing in other organism\" EXACT []\nis_a: GO:0031640 ! killing of cells of another organism\nis_a: GO:0044521 ! venom-mediated muscle damage in another organism\ncreated_by: jl\ncreation_date: 2012-02-27T12:33:57Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0044523\nname: venom-mediated disruption of extracellular matrix in another organism\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process that begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, damaging the extracellular matrix of a cell.\" [GOC:fj, GOC:jl, PMID:20398688, PMID:21150580, PMID:33460638, PMID:37006255, PMID:41241197]\nsynonym: \"envenomation resulting in damage of muscle extracellular matrix causing muscle necrosis in other organism\" NARROW []\nsynonym: \"envenomation resulting in damage of muscle extracellular matrix in another organism\" NARROW []\nsynonym: \"envenomation resulting in damage of muscle extracellular matrix in other organism\" NARROW []\nsynonym: \"venom spreading factor\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"venom-mediated extracellular matrix disassembly\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"venom-mediated extracellular matrix disassembly enhancing venom spread\" NARROW []\nis_a: GO:0140138 ! venom-mediated disruption of anatomical structure in another organism\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/3