{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778987374918,"sessionID":"ses_1cc17fd5bffeQIGMKJLRwjtTA3","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_R8UTgXecqR4EYKBYhdkuMds5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/references_cache/PMID_32024243.md","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/references_cache/PMID_32024243.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: reference_id: PMID:32024243\n3: title: Inflammatory Reaction Induced by Two Metalloproteinases Isolated from Bothrops atrox Venom and by Fragments Generated from the Hydrolysis of Basement Membrane Components.\n4: authors:\n5: - Almeida MT\n6: - Freitas-de-Sousa LA\n7: - Colombini M\n8: - Gimenes SNC\n9: - Kitano ES\n10: - Faquim-Mauro EL\n11: - Serrano SMT\n12: - Moura-da-Silva AM\n13: journal: Toxins (Basel)\n14: year: '2020'\n15: doi: 10.3390/toxins12020096\n16: keywords:\n17: - Animals\n18: - Basement Membrane\n19: - Bothrops\n20: - Crotalid Venoms/enzymology\n21: - Cytokines/immunology\n22: - Edema/immunology\n23: - Hydrolysis\n24: - Leukocyte Count\n25: - Male\n26: - Metalloproteases/toxicity\n27: - \"Mice, Inbred BALB C\"\n28: - Peritoneal Cavity\n29: content_type: abstract_only\n30: ---\n31: \n32: # Inflammatory Reaction Induced by Two Metalloproteinases Isolated from Bothrops atrox Venom and by Fragments Generated from the Hydrolysis of Basement Membrane Components.\n33: **Authors:** Almeida MT, Freitas-de-Sousa LA, Colombini M, Gimenes SNC, Kitano ES, Faquim-Mauro EL, Serrano SMT, Moura-da-Silva AM\n34: **Journal:** Toxins (Basel) (2020)\n35: **DOI:** [10.3390/toxins12020096](https://doi.org/10.3390/toxins12020096)\n36: \n37: ## Content\n38: \n39: 1. Toxins (Basel). 2020 Feb 2;12(2):96. doi: 10.3390/toxins12020096.\n40: \n41: Inflammatory Reaction Induced by Two Metalloproteinases Isolated from Bothrops \n42: atrox Venom and by Fragments Generated from the Hydrolysis of Basement Membrane \n43: Components.\n44: \n45: Almeida MT(1)(2), Freitas-de-Sousa LA(2), Colombini M(2), Gimenes SNC(2), Kitano \n46: ES(3), Faquim-Mauro EL(2), Serrano SMT(3), Moura-da-Silva AM(2).\n47: \n48: Author information:\n49: (1)Programa de Pós-Graduação em Ciências-Toxinologia, Instituto Butantan, São \n50: Paulo 05503-900, Brazil.\n51: (2)Laboratório de Imunopatologia, Instituto Butantan, São Paulo 05503-900, \n52: Brazil.\n53: (3)Laboratório de Toxinologia Aplicada, Center of Toxins, Immune-Response and \n54: Cell Signalig, CeTICS, Instituto Butantan, São Paulo 05503-900, Brazil.\n55: \n56: Snake venom metalloproteinases (SVMPs) play an important role in local tissue \n57: damage of snakebite patients, mostly by hydrolysis of basement membrane (BM) \n58: components. We evaluated the proinflammatory activity of SVMPs Atroxlysin-Ia \n59: (ATXL) and Batroxrhagin (BATXH) from Bothrops atrox venom and their hydrolysis \n60: products of Matrigel. BALB/c mice were injected with SVMPs (2 μg), for \n61: assessment of paw edema and peritoneal leukocyte accumulation. Both SVMPs \n62: induced edema, representing an increase of ~70% of the paw size. Leukocyte \n63: infiltrates reached levels of 6 × 106 with ATXL and 5 × 106 with BATXH. TNF-α \n64: was identified in the supernatant of BATXH-or venom-stimulated MPAC cells. \n65: Incubation of Matrigel with the SVMPs generated fragments, including peptides \n66: from Laminin, identified by LC-MS/MS. The Matrigel hydrolysis peptides caused \n67: edema that increased 30% the paw size and promoted leukocyte accumulation (4-5 × \n68: 106) to the peritoneal cavity, significantly higher than Matrigel control \n69: peptides 1 and 4 h after injection. Our findings suggest that ATXL and BATXH are \n70: involved in the inflammatory reaction observed in B. atrox envenomings by direct \n71: action on inflammatory cells or by releasing proinflammatory peptides from BM \n72: proteins that may amplify the direct action of SVMPs through activation of \n73: endogenous signaling pathways.\n74: \n75: DOI: 10.3390/toxins12020096\n76: PMCID: PMC7076977\n77: PMID: 32024243 [Indexed for MEDLINE]\n78: \n79: Conflict of interest statement: The authors declare no conflicts of interest.\n\n(End of file - total 79 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nreference_id: PMID:32024243\ntitle: Inflammatory Reaction Induced by Two Metalloproteinases Isolated from Bothrops atrox Venom and by Fragments Generated from the Hydrolysis of Basement Membrane Components.\nauthors:\n- Almeida MT\n- Freitas-de-Sousa LA\n- Colombini M\n- Gimenes SNC\n- Kitano ES\n- Faquim-Mauro EL\n- Serrano SMT\n- Moura-da-Silva AM\njournal: Toxins (Basel)\nyear: '2020'\ndoi: 10.3390/toxins12020096\nkeywords:\n- Animals\n- Basement Membrane\n- Bothrops\n- Crotalid Venoms/enzymology","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"references_cache/PMID_32024243.md","time":{"start":1778987374868,"end":1778987374904}},"id":"prt_e33e9190f001mVaRT7tumq41Js","sessionID":"ses_1cc17fd5bffeQIGMKJLRwjtTA3","messageID":"msg_e33e8fc77001kEsU2tTv7VFmum"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778987374918,"sessionID":"ses_1cc17fd5bffeQIGMKJLRwjtTA3","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_SGY6zfqQN2pBPEnyLlGekb2w","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/references_cache/PMID_19000915.md","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/references_cache/PMID_19000915.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: reference_id: PMID:19000915\n3: title: \"BthMP: a new weakly hemorrhagic metalloproteinase from Bothrops moojeni snake venom.\"\n4: authors:\n5: - Gomes MS\n6: - Mendes MM\n7: - de Oliveira F\n8: - de Andrade RM\n9: - Bernardes CP\n10: - Hamaguchi A\n11: - de Alcântara TM\n12: - Soares AM\n13: - Rodrigues VM\n14: - Homsi-Brandeburgo MI\n15: journal: Toxicon\n16: year: '2009'\n17: doi: 10.1016/j.toxicon.2008.10.007\n18: keywords:\n19: - Animals\n20: - Bothrops/physiology\n21: - Crotalid Venoms/enzymology\n22: - \"Dose-Response Relationship, Drug\"\n23: - Edema/chemically induced\n24: - Hemorrhage/chemically induced\n25: - Hindlimb\n26: - Male\n27: - \"Metalloproteases/chemistry, metabolism\"\n28: - Mice\n29: - \"Muscle, Skeletal/drug effects, pathology\"\n30: content_type: abstract_only\n31: ---\n32: \n33: # BthMP: a new weakly hemorrhagic metalloproteinase from Bothrops moojeni snake venom.\n34: **Authors:** Gomes MS, Mendes MM, de Oliveira F, de Andrade RM, Bernardes CP, Hamaguchi A, de Alcântara TM, Soares AM, Rodrigues VM, Homsi-Brandeburgo MI\n35: **Journal:** Toxicon (2009)\n36: **DOI:** [10.1016/j.toxicon.2008.10.007](https://doi.org/10.1016/j.toxicon.2008.10.007)\n37: \n38: ## Content\n39: \n40: 1. Toxicon. 2009 Jan;53(1):24-32. doi: 10.1016/j.toxicon.2008.10.007. Epub 2008\n41: Oct  17.\n42: \n43: BthMP: a new weakly hemorrhagic metalloproteinase from Bothrops moojeni snake \n44: venom.\n45: \n46: Gomes MS(1), Mendes MM, de Oliveira F, de Andrade RM, Bernardes CP, Hamaguchi A, \n47: de Alcântara TM, Soares AM, Rodrigues VM, Homsi-Brandeburgo MI.\n48: \n49: Author information:\n50: (1)Instituto de Genética e Bioquímica, Universidade Federal de Uberlândia (UFU), \n51: 38400-902 Uberlândia-MG, Brazil. mrochauesb@yahoo.com.br\n52: \n53: In this work, a new weakly hemorrhagic metalloproteinase (BthMP) was purified \n54: from Bothrops moojeni snake venom. This enzyme was homogeneous by native and \n55: SDS-PAGE. It showed a polypeptide chain of 23.5kDa, pI=7.1, and N-terminal \n56: blocked. BthMP is comprised of high proteolytic activity on casein, fibrin and \n57: bovine fibrinogen, with no coagulating, esterase or phospholipase A(2) \n58: activities; it was inhibited by EDTA, EGTA and 1,10-phenanthroline and \n59: maintained its activity on pH from 7.0 to 9.0 and temperature from 5-40 degrees \n60: C. Assays with metal ions showed that Ca(2+) is an activator, whereas Zn(2+) and \n61: Hg(2+) inhibited about 50 and 80% of its activity, respectively. The edema \n62: evidenced the important role of the toxin in the inflammatory activity of the \n63: venom. BthMP also caused unclotting, and provoked histological alterations in \n64: the gastrocnemius muscle of mice inducing hemorrhage, necrosis and leukocytic \n65: infiltrate. The molecular mass and the inhibition assays suggest that the \n66: metalloproteinase BthMP belongs to class P-I of SVMPs.\n67: \n68: DOI: 10.1016/j.toxicon.2008.10.007\n69: PMID: 19000915 [Indexed for MEDLINE]\n\n(End of file - total 69 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nreference_id: PMID:19000915\ntitle: \"BthMP: a new weakly hemorrhagic metalloproteinase from Bothrops moojeni snake venom.\"\nauthors:\n- Gomes MS\n- Mendes MM\n- de Oliveira F\n- de Andrade RM\n- Bernardes CP\n- Hamaguchi A\n- de Alcântara TM\n- Soares AM\n- Rodrigues VM\n- Homsi-Brandeburgo MI\njournal: Toxicon\nyear: '2009'\ndoi: 10.1016/j.toxicon.2008.10.007\nkeywords:\n- Animals\n- Bothrops/physiology","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"references_cache/PMID_19000915.md","time":{"start":1778987374891,"end":1778987374911}},"id":"prt_e33e91927001Nop6ep4WgKabMR","sessionID":"ses_1cc17fd5bffeQIGMKJLRwjtTA3","messageID":"msg_e33e8fc77001kEsU2tTv7VFmum"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778987374918,"sessionID":"ses_1cc17fd5bffeQIGMKJLRwjtTA3","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_tnR3Ah0Gore7q6j4Hgs7doXI","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/references_cache/PMID_26072684.md","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/references_cache/PMID_26072684.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: reference_id: PMID:26072684\n3: title: \"Inflammatory mediators involved in the paw edema and hyperalgesia induced by Batroxase, a metalloproteinase isolated from Bothrops atrox snake venom.\"\n4: authors:\n5: - De Toni LG\n6: - Menaldo DL\n7: - Cintra AC\n8: - Figueiredo MJ\n9: - de Souza AR\n10: - Maximiano WM\n11: - Jamur MC\n12: - Souza GE\n13: - Sampaio SV\n14: journal: Int Immunopharmacol\n15: year: '2015'\n16: doi: 10.1016/j.intimp.2015.06.001\n17: keywords:\n18: - Animals\n19: - Bothrops\n20: - Cell Degranulation/drug effects\n21: - Crotalid Venoms/enzymology\n22: - \"Edema/chemically induced, pathology\"\n23: - Foot/pathology\n24: - \"Hyperalgesia/chemically induced, pathology\"\n25: - Inflammation Mediators/metabolism\n26: - Male\n27: - Mast Cells/drug effects\n28: - Metalloproteases\n29: - Pain Measurement/drug effects\n30: - Rats\n31: - \"Rats, Wistar\"\n32: content_type: abstract_only\n33: ---\n34: \n35: # Inflammatory mediators involved in the paw edema and hyperalgesia induced by Batroxase, a metalloproteinase isolated from Bothrops atrox snake venom.\n36: **Authors:** De Toni LG, Menaldo DL, Cintra AC, Figueiredo MJ, de Souza AR, Maximiano WM, Jamur MC, Souza GE, Sampaio SV\n37: **Journal:** Int Immunopharmacol (2015)\n38: **DOI:** [10.1016/j.intimp.2015.06.001](https://doi.org/10.1016/j.intimp.2015.06.001)\n39: \n40: ## Content\n41: \n42: 1. Int Immunopharmacol. 2015 Sep;28(1):199-207. doi:\n43: 10.1016/j.intimp.2015.06.001.  Epub 2015 Jun 11.\n44: \n45: Inflammatory mediators involved in the paw edema and hyperalgesia induced by \n46: Batroxase, a metalloproteinase isolated from Bothrops atrox snake venom.\n47: \n48: De Toni LG(1), Menaldo DL(1), Cintra AC(1), Figueiredo MJ(2), de Souza AR(3), \n49: Maximiano WM(3), Jamur MC(3), Souza GE(2), Sampaio SV(4).\n50: \n51: Author information:\n52: (1)Departamento de Análises Clínicas, Toxicológicas e Bromatológicas, Faculdade \n53: de Ciências Farmacêuticas de Ribeirão Preto, USP, Ribeirão Preto-SP, Brazil.\n54: (2)Departamento de Física e Química, Faculdade de Ciências Farmacêuticas de \n55: Ribeirão Preto, USP, Ribeirão Preto-SP, Brazil.\n56: (3)Departamento de Biologia Celular e Molecular e Bioagentes Patogênicos, \n57: Faculdade de Medicina de Ribeirão Preto, Universidade de São Paulo, Ribeirão \n58: Preto-SP, Brazil.\n59: (4)Departamento de Análises Clínicas, Toxicológicas e Bromatológicas, Faculdade \n60: de Ciências Farmacêuticas de Ribeirão Preto, USP, Ribeirão Preto-SP, Brazil. \n61: Electronic address: suvilela@usp.br.\n62: \n63: Snake venom metalloproteinases have been described as responsible for several \n64: inflammatory effects. In this study, we investigated the edema and hyperalgesia \n65: induced in rats by Batroxase, a P-I metalloproteinase from Bothrops atrox venom, \n66: along with possible inflammatory mediators involved in these responses. \n67: Batroxase or sterile saline was injected into rat paws and the edema and \n68: hyperalgesic effects were evaluated for 6h by using a plethysmometer and a Von \n69: Frey system, respectively. Batroxase induced significant edematogenic and \n70: hyperalgesic peak responses in the first hours after administration. The \n71: inflammatory mediators involved in these responses were assayed by pretreatment \n72: of animals with synthesis inhibitors or receptor antagonists. Peak responses \n73: were significantly reduced by administration of the glucocorticoid \n74: dexamethasone, the H1 receptor antagonist diphenhydramine and the FLAP inhibitor \n75: MK-886. Rat paws injected with compound 48/80, a mast cell degranulating agent, \n76: followed by Batroxase injection resulted in significant reduction of the edema \n77: and hyperalgesia. However, Batroxase itself induced minor degranulation of \n78: RBL-2H3 mast cells in vitro. Additionally, the inflammatory responses did not \n79: seem to be related to prostaglandins, bradykinin or nitric oxide. Our results \n80: indicate a major involvement of histamine and leukotrienes in the edema and \n81: hyperalgesia induced by Batroxase, which could be related, at least in part, to \n82: mast cell degranulation.\n83: \n84: Copyright © 2015 Elsevier B.V. All rights reserved.\n85: \n86: DOI: 10.1016/j.intimp.2015.06.001\n87: PMID: 26072684 [Indexed for MEDLINE]\n\n(End of file - total 87 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nreference_id: PMID:26072684\ntitle: \"Inflammatory mediators involved in the paw edema and hyperalgesia induced by Batroxase, a metalloproteinase isolated from Bothrops atrox snake venom.\"\nauthors:\n- De Toni LG\n- Menaldo DL\n- Cintra AC\n- Figueiredo MJ\n- de Souza AR\n- Maximiano WM\n- Jamur MC\n- Souza GE\n- Sampaio SV\njournal: Int Immunopharmacol\nyear: '2015'\ndoi: 10.1016/j.intimp.2015.06.001\nkeywords:\n- Animals\n- Bothrops\n- Cell Degranulation/drug effects","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"references_cache/PMID_26072684.md","time":{"start":1778987374897,"end":1778987374915}},"id":"prt_e33e9192d001EeHdjXFoVev9f3","sessionID":"ses_1cc17fd5bffeQIGMKJLRwjtTA3","messageID":"msg_e33e8fc77001kEsU2tTv7VFmum"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1778987374929,"sessionID":"ses_1cc17fd5bffeQIGMKJLRwjtTA3","part":{"id":"prt_e33e9063a0011dHG4086wKfOUU","messageID":"msg_e33e8fc77001kEsU2tTv7VFmum","sessionID":"ses_1cc17fd5bffeQIGMKJLRwjtTA3","type":"text","text":"I have a safe new ID range to continue from `GO:7770071`. Next I’m reading the exact local stanzas for `venom-mediated edema` and the cached papers so the labels/defs/parentage are aligned with existing GO wording.","time":{"start":1778987370042,"end":1778987374927}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778987375823,"sessionID":"ses_1cc17fd5bffeQIGMKJLRwjtTA3","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_3bJ83BqcvX28SWFe4E4ghAbZ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/src/ontology/go-edit.obo","offset":263400,"limit":55},"output":"<path>/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/src/ontology/go-edit.obo</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n263400: replaced_by: GO:0006897\n263401: created_by: jl\n263402: creation_date: 2011-12-21T03:37:11Z\n263403: \n263404: [Term]\n263405: id: GO:0044398\n263406: name: venom-mediated edema\n263407: namespace: biological_process\n263408: def: \"A process by which an organism causes swelling of soft tissues in another organism via the action of a venom. Edema is the result of excess water accumulation in tissues.\" [PMID:20562011]\n263409: synonym: \"envenomation resulting in induction of edema in another organism\" EXACT []\n263410: synonym: \"envenomation resulting in induction of edema in other organism\" EXACT []\n263411: synonym: \"envenomation resulting in induction of oedema in other organism\" EXACT []\n263412: is_a: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biological process\n263413: property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29375\" xsd:anyURI\n263414: property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29851\" xsd:anyURI\n263415: created_by: jl\n263416: creation_date: 2011-12-21T03:57:27Z\n263417: \n263418: [Term]\n263419: id: GO:0044399\n263420: name: multi-species biofilm formation\n263421: namespace: biological_process\n263422: alt_id: GO:0044400\n263423: alt_id: GO:0044401\n263424: alt_id: GO:0090607\n263425: alt_id: GO:0090608\n263426: def: \"A process in which planktonically growing microorganisms of different species grow at a liquid-air interface or on a solid substrate under the flow of a liquid and produce extracellular polymers that facilitate matrix formation, resulting in a change in the organisms' growth rate and gene transcription.\" [GOC:cc, GOC:di, GOC:tb]\n263427: synonym: \"multi-species biofilm formation in or on host organism\" NARROW []\n263428: synonym: \"multi-species biofilm formation on inanimate substrate\" NARROW []\n263429: synonym: \"multi-species submerged biofilm formation\" NARROW []\n263430: synonym: \"multi-species surface biofilm formation\" RELATED []\n263431: is_a: GO:0042710 ! biofilm formation\n263432: is_a: GO:0044403 ! biological process involved in symbiotic interaction\n263433: \n263434: [Term]\n263435: id: GO:0044402\n263436: name: obsolete competition with other organism\n263437: namespace: biological_process\n263438: def: \"OBSOLETE. Any process in which an organism within a multispecies community gains an advantage in growth or survival over another organism of a different species in that community.\" [GOC:cc]\n263439: comment: This term was obsoleted because it is outside the scope of GO.\n263440: synonym: \"competition with another organism\" EXACT [GOC:bf]\n263441: synonym: \"interspecies competition\" BROAD []\n263442: property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/18568\" xsd:anyURI\n263443: is_obsolete: true\n263444: \n263445: [Term]\n263446: id: GO:0044403\n263447: name: biological process involved in symbiotic interaction\n263448: namespace: biological_process\n263449: alt_id: GO:0043298\n263450: alt_id: GO:0044404\n263451: alt_id: GO:0072519\n263452: alt_id: GO:0085031\n263453: def: \"A process carried out by gene products in an organism that enable the organism to engage in a symbiotic relationship, a more or less intimate association, with another organism. The various forms of symbiosis include parasitism, in which the association is disadvantageous or destructive to one of the organisms; mutualism, in which the association is advantageous, or often necessary to one or both and not harmful to either; and commensalism, in which one member of the association benefits while the other is not affected. However, mutualism, parasitism, and commensalism are often not discrete categories of interactions and should rather be perceived as a continuum of interaction ranging from parasitism to mutualism. In fact, the direction of a symbiotic interaction can change during the lifetime of the symbionts due to developmental changes as well as changes in the biotic/abiotic environment in which the interaction occurs. Microscopic symbionts are often referred to as endosymbionts.\" [GOC:cc, PMID:31257129]\n263454: subset: goslim_chembl\n\n(Showing lines 263400-263454 of 618085. Use offset=263455 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"replaced_by: GO:0006897\ncreated_by: jl\ncreation_date: 2011-12-21T03:37:11Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0044398\nname: venom-mediated edema\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process by which an organism causes swelling of soft tissues in another organism via the action of a venom. Edema is the result of excess water accumulation in tissues.\" [PMID:20562011]\nsynonym: \"envenomation resulting in induction of edema in another organism\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"envenomation resulting in induction of edema in other organism\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"envenomation resulting in induction of oedema in other organism\" EXACT []\nis_a: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biological process\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29375\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29851\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: jl\ncreation_date: 2011-12-21T03:57:27Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0044399","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"src/ontology/go-edit.obo","time":{"start":1778987374845,"end":1778987375821}},"id":"prt_e33e918f80011nrWqCx4SNaqiH","sessionID":"ses_1cc17fd5bffeQIGMKJLRwjtTA3","messageID":"msg_e33e8fc77001kEsU2tTv7VFmum"}}
