{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778987440116,"sessionID":"ses_1cc17fd5bffeQIGMKJLRwjtTA3","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_iMyMyyNROkNvdNGEee4aJW1a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/src/ontology/go-edit.obo","offset":222960,"limit":40},"output":"<path>/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/src/ontology/go-edit.obo</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n222960: created_by: bf\n222961: creation_date: 2011-03-17T10:58:57Z\n222962: \n222963: [Term]\n222964: id: GO:0035738\n222965: name: venom-mediated perturbation of biological process\n222966: namespace: biological_process\n222967: def: \"A process by which an organism alters or subverts a biological process in another organism via the action of a venom. Venoms are injected into the prey by a bite or a sting. Venoms cause their biological effects via the many toxins that they contain; some venoms are complex mixtures of toxins of differing types. Venoms can serve as predation mechanisms or defense responses.\" [Wikipedia:Venom]\n222968: synonym: \"envenomation\" EXACT []\n222969: synonym: \"envenomation perturbing biological process\" EXACT []\n222970: synonym: \"envenomation resulting in modification of morphology or physiology of other organism\" EXACT []\n222971: synonym: \"envenomation resulting in modulation of process in another organism\" EXACT []\n222972: synonym: \"envenomation resulting in modulation of process in other organism\" EXACT []\n222973: xref: Wikipedia:Venom\n222974: is_a: GO:0035821 ! modulation of process of another organism\n222975: property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/18605\" xsd:anyURI\n222976: property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29375\" xsd:anyURI\n222977: created_by: bf\n222978: creation_date: 2011-03-17T10:59:27Z\n222979: \n222980: [Term]\n222981: id: GO:0035739\n222982: name: CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell proli