te inflammatory response\" BROAD []\n\n  Line 19409: intersection_of: GO:0001821 ! histamine secretion\n\n  Line 19411: relationship: part_of GO:0002349 ! histamine production involved in inflammatory response\n\n  Line 20360: name: leukotriene production involved in inflammatory response\n\n  Line 20362: def: \"The synthesis or release of any leukotriene following a stimulus as part of an inflammatory response, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\n\n  Line 20363: synonym: \"leukotriene production involved in acute inflammatory response\" BROAD []\n\n  Line 20491: name: histamine secretion by mast cell\n\n  Line 20493: def: \"The regulated release of histamine by a mast cell or group of mast cells.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\n\n  Line 20494: is_a: GO:0002441 ! histamine secretion involved in inflammatory response\n\n  Line 20495: intersection_of: GO:0001821 ! histamine secretion\n\n  Line 20512: name: histamine secretion by platelet\n\n  Line 20514: def: \"The regulated release of histamine by a platelet or group of platelets.\" [GOC:add, PMID:9117517]\n\n  Line 20515: is_a: GO:0002441 ! histamine secretion involved in inflammatory response\n\n  Line 20516: intersection_of: GO:0001821 ! histamine secretion\n\n  Line 20533: name: histamine secretion by basophil\n\n  Line 20535: def: \"The regulated release of histamine by a basophil or group of basophils.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\n\n  Line 20536: is_a: GO:0002441 ! histamine secretion involved in inflammatory response\n\n  Line 20537: intersection_of: GO:0001821 ! histamine secretion\n\n  Line 20545: def: \"An inflammatory response driven by antigen recognition by antibodies bound to Fc receptors on mast cells, occurring within minutes after exposure of a sensitized individual to the antigen, and leading to the release of a variety of inflammatory mediators such as histamines.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\n\n  Line 20553: def: \"An inflammatory response driven by antigen recognition by antibodies bound to Fc receptors basophils, occurring within minutes after exposure of a sensitized individual to the antigen, and leading to the release of a variety of inflammatory mediators such as histamines.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\n\n  Line 20570: def: \"The regulated exocytosis of secretory granules containing preformed mediators such as histamine, serotonin, and neutral proteases by a basophil.\" [GOC:add, ISBN:0781735149]\n\n  Line 20704: def: \"The regulated exocytosis of secretory granules containing preformed mediators such as histamine and serotonin by a platelet.\" [GOC:add]\n\n  Line 25010: name: leukotriene-C(4) hydrolase activity\n\n  Line 25012: def: \"Catalysis of the reaction leukotriene C(4) + H2O= leukotriene D(4) + L-glutamate.\" [PMID:9774450, RHEA:31563]\n\n  Line 25013: comment: The mouse enzyme is specific for leukotriene C(4), while the human enzyme also has considerable activity toward glutathione and oxidized glutathione (cf. EC:3.4.19.13). PMID:9774450 cites that the mouse form of this enzyme failed to measure activity towards glutathione.\n\n  Line 31620: def: \"Catalysis of the synthesis of beta-alanyl amine conjugate from a precursor biogenic amine, such as dopamine or histamine.\" [GOC:bf, PMID:12900414, PMID:12957543, PMID:25229196]\n\n  Line 35611: def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: (5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z)-eicosatetraenoate + O2 = H2O + leukotriene A4.\" [RHEA:32307]\n\n  Line 35622: synonym: \"leukotriene A4 synthase\" BROAD [EC:1.13.11.34]\n\n  Line 35623: synonym: \"leukotriene-A(4) synthase activity\" NARROW [EC:1.13.11.34]\n\n  Line 35624: synonym: \"leukotriene-A4 synthase activity\" RELATED [EC:1.13.11.34]\n\n  Line 35646: synonym: \"leukotriene A4 synthase\" BROAD [EC:1.13.11.31]\n\n  Line 41368: def: \"Catalysis of the reaction: L-histidine = histamine + CO2.\" [EC:4.1.1.22]\n\n  Line 41369: synonym: \"L-histidine carboxy-lyase (histamine-forming)\" RELATED [EC:4.1.1.22]\n\n  Line 42368